==Recognition of the PRC after it was seated at the UN== The Republic of China, which had occupied [[China and the United Nations|China's seat at the United Nations]] since 1945, was effectively expelled on 25 October 1971. Its seat was taken over by the People's Republic of China from 15 November 1971, and the migration of relations to the PRC soon followed among members of the [[Western Bloc]], except for the United Kingdom, France, Canada, Italy and the [[Scandinavia]]n Countries which had previously established diplomatic relations.
